Traumatic Brain Injury (TBI) Personal Injury Lawyer

























Menu











 Las Vegas702.474.6400   Los Angeles310.552.2050 







Previous
Next










Brain Injury


Free Case Evaluation








We Protect Traumatic Brain Injury Victims
Traumatic Brain Injury (TBI) cases can be mild, moderate or severe.  They can affect people in ways that maybe only a few friends and family members can discern.  Sometimes you can suffer a traumatic brain injury without losing consciousness.  If you feel that you have suffered from a mild TBI or you lost consciousness during an accident and have problems with headaches, memory loss or concentration you may have serious injuries which require medical work up.
If you have suffered from what some may classify as a mild traumatic brain injury it can be very disabling and have an effect on you for the rest of your life.  In litigating mild traumatic brain injury cases it is very important that you see the proper neuro-psychologist and have the proper imaging done by a neuro-radiologist. These cases must be explored to their full capacity.  If you or a loved one has been injured and you think that the injury has resulted in a mild traumatic brain injury or concussion which has changed that person in a way that may not be obvious to a stranger please Peter Goldstein, a personal injury attornet which handled many of these cases and know the proper experts and medical doctors to evaluate your injuries.
 Call the Law Office of Peter Goldstein today for a FREE consultation (702) 474-6400.






