BadgesClaimed Lawyer  ProfileSocial MediaSummaryFree Consultation & Support    Trial attorney Peter Goldstein graduated from the University of Southern California with a bachelor's degree in 1977, and then earned his juris doctor from Whittier School of Law in 1985 with honors.  He and his family live in Las Vegas but maintain a residence in Culver City, California. Peter has tried over 80 trials including over 30 jury trials, and is familiar with the judges, mediators and arbitrators in Southern Nevada and Southern California.  His practice areas include personal injury, car accidents, bicycle accidents, motorcycle accidents, premises liability, police misconduct and civil rights, wrongful death, and business litigation.  Peter Goldstein is a member of Nevada Justice Association and Consumer Attorneys Association of Los Angeles  Your Personal Injury Law Firm in Southern California and Southern Nevada   I will do everything necessary to successfully resolve your personal injury, slip and fall, car accident, dog bite, police misconduct, or business dispute case.  I will oversee every aspect of the case from beginning to end to get you the best result. If I don't win your case, you don't pay me anything.  Call me today for a free consultation.  CASE RESULTS  May 2015, Char v. Smith's Food & Drug Centers, personal injury/trip and fall case: my client was an elderly woman who tripped and fell over a box negligently left on the floor in an aisleway at a grocery store by store employees. My client fractured her wrist and suffered permanent nerve damage in the fall. The case proceeded to a trial by jury that awarded my client $100,440.  November 2014, Argumedo v. Exxon Mobil Corporation, workplace accident/personal injury: my client was a fuel tanker truck driver injured while operating a defective fuel pump hose. His injuries rendered him incapable of working as a truck driver again. The case settled for $128,000 for my client.  May 2012, Brown v. City of San Bernardino, 